.TH HSH 1 "June 2026" "Holberton School" "User Commands"  
  
.SH NAME  
hsh \- a simple UNIX command interpreter  
  
.SH SYNOPSIS  
.B ./hsh  
  
.SH DESCRIPTION  
.B hsh  
is a simple command line interpreter written in C language. It receives commands  
from standard input and executes them, showing the results on the screen.  
  
The shell operates in two modes: an interactive one, when it shows a prompt, and  
a non-interactive one, when it reads commands from a file or pipe.  
  
.SH COMMANDS  
The shell performs commands that are entered by the user.  
  
Examples are:  
  
.B ls  
  
.B pwd  
  
.B /bin/ls  
  
The shell supports the built-in command:  
  
.B exit  
which terminates the process.  
  
.SH RETURN VALUE  
The shell returns the exit status of the last command performed.  
  
.SH EXAMPLES  
Start the shell:  
  
.nf  
./hsh  
($) ls  
main.c shell.c  
($) exit  
.fi  
  
Start in non-interactive mode:  
  
.nf  
echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh  
.fi  
  
